Advocate Busisiwe Mkhwebane released her report weeks ago where she ordered the Special Investigating Unit to recover more than R1 billion from Absa. CAPE TOWN - Absa Bank has filed court papers to be joined as a co-applicant in the Reserve Bank s application to review and set aside the Public Protector s remedial action regarding the apartheid era Bankorp bailout.Advocate Busisiwe Mkhwebane released her report weeks ago where she ordered the Special Investigating Unit to recover more than R1 billion from Absa.She also ordered Parliament to amend the section of the Constitution which prescribes the Reserve Bank's mandate.More information to follow.